header.gameNote: ATLANTIC SUN MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - QUARTERFINAL AT MACON GA

article.headline: ETSU 68, North Florida 66
article.story: MACON, Ga. -- Isiah Brown scored 22 points as East Tennessee State defeated North Florida 68-66 Thursday in the Atlantic Sun Conference tournament quarterfinals. The fourth-seeded Buccaneers (17-13) will face top seed Belmont in the semifinals Friday night. ETSU and Belmont have won the past six tournaments, with ETSU winning in 2009 and 2010. Brown blocked a 3-point try by Parker Smith of the fifth-seeded Ospreys (16-16) with ETSU ahead 66-64. The block -- which gave Brown a school career record of 182 -- led to a Marcus Dubose layup and a 68-64 lead with 48 seconds left. A jumper by Smith, whose 17 points led the Ospreys, made it a two-point game with 25 seconds left. North Florida got the ball back after Dubose missed a free throw, but Smith's 3-point try was off the mark with 2 seconds remaining. North Florida defeated ETSU 59-55 in the semifinals of last year's tournament.
